## 9. Out of scope

- **Other float formats** (float32, float128, bfloat16): the same analysis should transfer but with their respective subnormal floor values. Logged for separate per-format audit.
- **Non-binary radix** (decimal IEEE 754): subnormal structure differs; separate theorem.
- **Non-default rounding modes**: the first part of BACL (real-difference is integer-multiple) is rounding-mode-independent; the second part (float representation equals exact value) depends on RN.
- **Negative or zero values**: trivial sign extension; deferred.
- **Overflow boundary**: separate concern from subnormal.

